256
00:10:53,821 --> 00:10:55,021
Who brought that kid
into the er,

257
00:10:55,089 --> 00:10:56,723
Then maybe we're taking
the wrong person's word

258
00:10:56,790 --> 00:10:58,091
For what
really happened.

259
00:10:58,158 --> 00:10:59,092
Whoa, whoa.

260
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:00,893
You think a cop
hurt this kid?

261
00:11:00,961 --> 00:11:02,395
Dylan seems to.

262
00:11:02,463 --> 00:11:03,496
I mean,
he's a cop, right?

263
00:11:03,564 --> 00:11:04,864
They--they're
people.

264
00:11:04,932 --> 00:11:05,965
There can be good
ones, bad ones.

265
00:11:06,033 --> 00:11:07,600
Yeah, but, i mean,
killing a kid?

266
00:11:07,668 --> 00:11:10,236
Look, he went
back to work right
before dylan died.

267
00:11:10,304 --> 00:11:11,771
Maybe he went back
too soon.

268
00:11:12,773 --> 00:11:13,840
You're thinking ptsd?

269
00:11:13,907 --> 00:11:15,441
That would make
a man volatile.

270
00:11:15,509 --> 00:11:18,111
I just want to know
where that skateboarding
story came from.

271
00:11:19,780 --> 00:11:22,215
Ok, i will find out
as much as i can.

272
00:11:22,282 --> 00:11:23,349
Thank you.

273
00:11:23,417 --> 00:11:25,518
After i get
your car outta hock.

274
00:11:32,626 --> 00:11:34,193
Hey, uh, buddy.

275
00:11:34,261 --> 00:11:36,562
Um, i've been waiting,
like, 20 minutes
for this car to come out.

276
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:38,297
Do you think--
you should talk to him.

277
00:11:38,365 --> 00:11:40,633
Sorry. thanks.

278
00:11:40,701 --> 00:11:42,802
Hey.
hey.

279
00:11:44,038 --> 00:11:46,773
Don't tell me.
you couldn't find the car.

280
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:48,808
No, we found it.

281
00:11:48,876 --> 00:11:51,344
Good. thanks.

282
00:11:51,412 --> 00:11:54,313
Thing is, your car
was accidentally tagged
for a drug search.

283
00:11:54,381 --> 00:11:56,449
What?

284
00:11:56,517 --> 00:11:58,484
It kinda got stripped.

285
00:11:58,552 --> 00:11:59,585
Down to the frame.

286
00:11:59,653 --> 00:12:01,654
What do you mean,
down to the frame?

287
00:12:01,722 --> 00:12:03,523
You know your
steering wheel,

288
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:04,891
Seats, stereo
system, stuff
like that?

289
00:12:04,958 --> 00:12:05,892
Right.

290
00:12:05,959 --> 00:12:08,061
They're
pretty much gone.

291
00:12:08,128 --> 00:12:09,429
Tell me you're kidding.

292
00:12:09,496 --> 00:12:11,097
Sorry, bro,
it's no joke.

293
00:12:11,165 --> 00:12:14,100
But it was totally
our bad, so you will
get reimbursed.

294
00:12:14,168 --> 00:12:15,101
Yeah.

295
00:12:15,169 --> 00:12:17,036
You know, my wife
really liked this car.

296
00:12:17,104 --> 00:12:19,572
At least she'll
get to go shopping
for a new one.

297
00:12:21,308 --> 00:12:22,475
All right, thanks.
yeah.

298
00:12:22,543 --> 00:12:24,210
Wait a minute,
wait a minute.

299
00:12:24,278 --> 00:12:26,713
You said
that someone told you

300
00:12:26,780 --> 00:12:29,148
Accidentally to strip
my wife's car?

301
00:12:29,216 --> 00:12:30,149
Yeah.

302
00:12:30,217 --> 00:12:31,451
Who?

303
00:12:31,518 --> 00:12:33,586
That, i don't know.

304
00:12:33,654 --> 00:12:35,154
There's no paperwork
on it,

305
00:12:35,222 --> 00:12:36,556
Which is one
of the reasons

306
00:12:36,623 --> 00:12:37,824
Why we realized
it was a mistake.

307
00:12:39,126 --> 00:12:41,494
A mistake, huh?
yeah.

308
00:12:41,562 --> 00:12:42,695
All right.

309
00:12:42,763 --> 00:12:44,397
Thanks.

310
00:12:44,465 --> 00:12:45,765
Yeah.

311
00:12:50,904 --> 00:12:52,805
he made a mistake?

312
00:12:52,873 --> 00:12:55,208
So, he killed my car?

313
00:12:56,410 --> 00:12:57,977
All right. you know
what? that's personal.

314
00:12:58,045 --> 00:13:00,379
I just think you need
to be more careful,
that's all.

315
00:13:00,447 --> 00:13:01,514
Melinda, on phone:
don't worry about it.

316
00:13:01,582 --> 00:13:03,583
I know how
to handle this guy.

317
00:13:08,288 --> 00:13:09,388
Phew.

318
00:13:11,525 --> 00:13:13,259
Officer ramsey?

319
00:13:13,327 --> 00:13:14,727
Hi. melinda gordon.

320
00:13:14,795 --> 00:13:16,462
We met over there
the other night.

321
00:13:16,530 --> 00:13:18,498
Did dr. james get
his tail light fixed?

322
00:13:18,565 --> 00:13:20,133
Oh, you scared him
straight.

323
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,300
You have a knack
for that.

324
00:13:21,368 --> 00:13:22,902
Good to know.

325
00:13:22,970 --> 00:13:24,804
Which is what i'm hoping
that you will do

326
00:13:24,872 --> 00:13:26,472
With the skateboarders
around here,

327
00:13:26,540 --> 00:13:28,474
'cause they're always
in front of my store.

328
00:13:28,542 --> 00:13:30,109
Mostly kids, teenagers.

329
00:13:30,177 --> 00:13:31,410
And you're
concerned about?

330
00:13:31,478 --> 00:13:32,812
Safety.

331
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,747
Especially after that--

332
00:13:34,815 --> 00:13:37,016
That young kid died
in a skateboarding accident.

333
00:13:37,084 --> 00:13:38,951
I don't think
most skateboarding
accidents

334
00:13:39,019 --> 00:13:39,952
Are that serious.

335
00:13:40,020 --> 00:13:41,954
Still.

336
00:13:42,022 --> 00:13:43,256
How's his family doing?

337
00:13:43,323 --> 00:13:44,457
I wouldn't know.

338
00:13:44,525 --> 00:13:46,259
That death wasn't
a police matter.

339
00:13:46,326 --> 00:13:47,460
It was an accident,
not a crime.

340
00:13:47,528 --> 00:13:49,662
No, no, right.

341
00:13:49,730 --> 00:13:51,063
Right. it's just
i had--i had heard

342
00:13:51,131 --> 00:13:52,865
That he was in trouble
with the law?

343
00:13:52,933 --> 00:13:54,534
Not that i know of.

344
00:13:54,601 --> 00:13:56,469
Not here in
grandview anyway.

345
00:13:56,537 --> 00:13:58,604
And not that
it makes his death
any less tragic.

346
00:13:58,672 --> 00:14:01,207
No, i--i didn't
mean that.

347
00:14:05,846 --> 00:14:08,214
Ms. gordon.

348
00:14:08,282 --> 00:14:11,484
I've been patrolling
the square for almost
a month now

349
00:14:11,552 --> 00:14:13,452
And i haven't noticed
any skateboarders.

350
00:14:20,494 --> 00:14:22,228
Ahh! that is
a sandwich.

351
00:14:24,064 --> 00:14:25,364
Eli, come right in.

352
00:14:25,432 --> 00:14:27,033
Hello.

353
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:29,769
Well, since i figured
you're a one-car household

354
00:14:29,837 --> 00:14:31,204
And i just happened
to be passing by,

355
00:14:31,271 --> 00:14:33,072
I wanted to see
if you needed a ride
back to the hospital.

356
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:34,207
Oh, thanks.

357
00:14:34,274 --> 00:14:36,042
I'm working a double.
it's the worst.

358
00:14:36,109 --> 00:14:39,345
I was going to ride
my bike, but since
you were, um,

359
00:14:39,413 --> 00:14:41,247
Just passing by?

360
00:14:41,315 --> 00:14:42,815
My wife put you up
to this, didn't she?

361
00:14:42,883 --> 00:14:45,017
She felt bad
about monopolizing your car.

362
00:14:45,085 --> 00:14:46,919
You heard what happened,
didn't you?

363
00:14:46,987 --> 00:14:48,321
They didn't
just tow her car.

364
00:14:48,388 --> 00:14:49,522
They trashed it.

365
00:14:49,590 --> 00:14:51,557
I know. who knew
mistakes like that
could happen?

366
00:14:51,625 --> 00:14:54,327
I don't think
anybody made
a mistake.

367
00:14:54,394 --> 00:14:55,628
What do you mean?

368
00:14:56,964 --> 00:14:59,732
I don't want to sound
like i'm overreacting,

369
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:01,567
But you stirred
something up.

370
00:15:01,635 --> 00:15:03,236
Me?

371
00:15:03,303 --> 00:15:04,237
You and melinda.

372
00:15:04,304 --> 00:15:05,738
Well, that's
kinda what we do.

373
00:15:05,806 --> 00:15:07,940
We stir things up
and then cross them over.

374
00:15:08,008 --> 00:15:08,941
Something like that.

375
00:15:09,009 --> 00:15:10,376
Eli, i'm serious, ok?

376
00:15:10,444 --> 00:15:11,577
I used to be
a paramedic.

377
00:15:11,645 --> 00:15:13,713
I know a little bit
about cops and how
they work.

378
00:15:13,780 --> 00:15:15,781
Any way you slice this,
there could be trouble.

379
00:15:15,849 --> 00:15:17,617
Ramsey's haunted
for a reason.

380
00:15:17,684 --> 00:15:19,118
Well, let me try
to say it simply.

381
00:15:19,186 --> 00:15:20,887
If ramsey's a good cop,

382
00:15:20,954 --> 00:15:22,822
He's gonna do
a lot to protect his
reputation, all right?

383
00:15:22,890 --> 00:15:23,923
If he's bad cop--

384
00:15:23,991 --> 00:15:25,658
Who might have
possibly killed a kid.

385
00:15:25,726 --> 00:15:27,093
A high school kid.
right.

386
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:29,428
I hear you.
i'm not saying
stand by and do nothing.

387
00:15:29,496 --> 00:15:31,564
No, you're saying
just don't play games
with my wife's safety.

388
00:15:31,632 --> 00:15:33,532
Yeah, yeah.
i am saying that.

389
00:15:37,037 --> 00:15:38,304
I worry about her, ok?

390
00:15:38,372 --> 00:15:39,705
So do i.

391
00:15:41,508 --> 00:15:42,541
I know.

392
00:15:42,609 --> 00:15:44,277
No, listen. jim.
melinda's my best friend.

393
00:15:44,344 --> 00:15:45,544
I know.

394
00:15:45,612 --> 00:15:46,612
No, you don't.

395
00:15:48,949 --> 00:15:51,884
I haven't had a friend
like that since i was
12 years old.

396
00:15:51,952 --> 00:15:53,219
Someone who
i've looked up to

397
00:15:53,287 --> 00:15:55,421
And i can learn
things from.

398
00:15:55,489 --> 00:15:57,723
I don't want
anything bad to happen
to her, either.

399
00:15:57,791 --> 00:16:00,793
Well then,
hurry up and figure out
what this ghost wants.

400
00:16:00,861 --> 00:16:03,729
Because if this
car thing's a message
from ramsey,

401
00:16:03,797 --> 00:16:05,431
He's on to her.

402
00:16:05,499 --> 00:16:06,666
And you.

403
00:16:08,769 --> 00:16:11,270
He didn't even
bat an eye when i
mentioned dylan.

404
00:16:11,338 --> 00:16:12,338
And this was
after my car

405
00:16:12,406 --> 00:16:13,739
Was mysteriously
destroyed.

406
00:16:13,807 --> 00:16:15,274
I mean, he is
one cool customer.

407
00:16:15,342 --> 00:16:17,343
Maybe he's
not a cool customer.

408
00:16:17,411 --> 00:16:18,711
Maybe he's just innocent.

409
00:16:18,779 --> 00:16:20,012
Seriously?

410
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:22,248
Since when did
you become a fan
of officer ramsey's?

411
00:16:22,316 --> 00:16:23,716
Since never.

412
00:16:23,784 --> 00:16:24,917
But it's possible
he was telling
the truth

413
00:16:24,985 --> 00:16:27,053
About dylan not having
a juvie record.

414
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:29,255
So, maybe they didn't
know each other.

415
00:16:29,323 --> 00:16:30,456
Look.

416
00:16:30,524 --> 00:16:32,758
I just talked
to detective blair
10 minutes ago.

417
00:16:32,826 --> 00:16:34,327
She told me
off the record.

418
00:16:34,394 --> 00:16:36,095
Whatever happened
between them,

419
00:16:36,163 --> 00:16:37,129
It's personal.

420
00:16:37,197 --> 00:16:38,531
That's why dylan
was at his house

421
00:16:38,598 --> 00:16:40,833
And that's why
he said that ramsey is
out for revenge.

422
00:16:40,901 --> 00:16:42,201
Were they neighbors?

423
00:16:42,269 --> 00:16:43,402
Lots of neighbors
hate each other.

424
00:16:43,470 --> 00:16:44,971
No, i checked.

425
00:16:45,038 --> 00:16:46,839
And they lived across
town from each other.

426
00:16:46,907 --> 00:16:48,574
Well, maybe it was
some sort of family feud.

427
00:16:48,642 --> 00:16:50,209
Family feud?

428
00:16:50,277 --> 00:16:52,078
Yeah.

429
00:16:52,145 --> 00:16:53,546
Wait a minute. family.

430
00:16:53,613 --> 00:16:56,282
He has a daughter.
she's in high school.

431
00:16:56,350 --> 00:16:57,550
What if she and dylan
were dating

432
00:16:57,617 --> 00:16:59,452
And that's how he got
on ramsey's bad side?

433
00:16:59,519 --> 00:17:01,253
And then some.

434
00:17:01,321 --> 00:17:03,823
Wow. so,
hats off to dylan.

435
00:17:03,890 --> 00:17:06,325
It takes a lot of cojones
to date a cop's daughter.

436
00:17:11,631 --> 00:17:13,933
Ok, i'll call
you later.

437
00:17:14,001 --> 00:17:14,934
Hi.

438
00:17:15,002 --> 00:17:16,902
Hi. uh, i'm melinda gordon.

439
00:17:16,970 --> 00:17:19,205
Yeah, we met down
at the station.

440
00:17:19,272 --> 00:17:21,140
I didn't think i made
a very good impression.

441
00:17:21,208 --> 00:17:22,541
Sorry about that.

442
00:17:22,609 --> 00:17:24,543
That place
kinda brings out
the worst in me.

443
00:17:24,611 --> 00:17:25,945
It's ok.

444
00:17:27,581 --> 00:17:29,648
Sometimes my dad
just gets to me.

445
00:17:29,716 --> 00:17:32,918
He's way overprotective,
you know?

446
00:17:32,986 --> 00:17:35,855
My dad wasn't exactly
the hands-on type, so.

447
00:17:35,922 --> 00:17:37,023
Lucky you.

448
00:17:37,090 --> 00:17:39,492
If dad could have me
home-schooled,
he would.

449
00:17:39,559 --> 00:17:41,227
Thankfully he works,
and my mom,

450
00:17:41,294 --> 00:17:42,928
She took off
a long time ago,

451
00:17:42,996 --> 00:17:44,463
So he's got no choice.

452
00:17:44,531 --> 00:17:46,499
He has to uncage me
for school.

453
00:17:48,201 --> 00:17:50,803
Did you need directions
to the main office
or anything?

454
00:17:50,871 --> 00:17:52,471
No, actually, i was
hoping to run into you,

455
00:17:52,539 --> 00:17:54,173
'cause i wanted
to talk to you.

456
00:17:54,241 --> 00:17:56,308
Yeah? what about?

457
00:17:56,376 --> 00:17:57,510
Dylan hale.

458
00:17:57,577 --> 00:18:00,079
The kid who died
in the skateboarding accident?

459
00:18:01,448 --> 00:18:03,749
What? why?

460
00:18:03,817 --> 00:18:05,718
Did you know him?

461
00:18:05,786 --> 00:18:06,886
Everybody did.

462
00:18:06,953 --> 00:18:08,421
It's not exactly
a big school.

463
00:18:10,323 --> 00:18:11,957
Anne-marie,
i understand.

464
00:18:12,025 --> 00:18:13,059
About your dad.

465
00:18:13,126 --> 00:18:14,226
Being on your case
all the time.

466
00:18:14,294 --> 00:18:16,162
It had to have
been hard on you.

467
00:18:16,229 --> 00:18:17,329
Both of you.

468
00:18:17,397 --> 00:18:18,697
I don't know
what you're
talking about.

469
00:18:18,765 --> 00:18:20,199
Were you and dylan dating?

470
00:18:20,267 --> 00:18:21,834
No.

471
00:18:21,902 --> 00:18:23,102
Look, i gotta go.

472
00:18:24,704 --> 00:18:26,806
Ok, look. wait.

473
00:18:29,076 --> 00:18:30,776
This is going to sound
really strange,

474
00:18:30,844 --> 00:18:33,045
But i have a gift.

475
00:18:33,113 --> 00:18:34,513
I see ghosts.

476
00:18:34,581 --> 00:18:36,415
And i've seen
dylan's.
what?

477
00:18:36,483 --> 00:18:37,817
He doesn't
belong here

478
00:18:37,884 --> 00:18:39,418
And there is a reason
that he can't move on,

479
00:18:39,486 --> 00:18:40,786
And i think you know
what it is.

480
00:18:40,854 --> 00:18:43,022
Stop it.
please. he needs
your help.

481
00:18:43,090 --> 00:18:45,591
I told you.

482
00:18:45,659 --> 00:18:47,526
I don't know what you're
talking about.

483
00:19:27,094 --> 00:19:28,294
I mean,
she couldn't wait
to get away from me.

484
00:19:28,362 --> 00:19:29,495
That's when
she dropped it.

485
00:19:29,563 --> 00:19:31,263
You think dylan
gave her this thing?

486
00:19:31,331 --> 00:19:32,798
It has to have
some significance.

487
00:19:32,866 --> 00:19:34,300
I mean, i saw him get
clubbed in the head.

488
00:19:34,368 --> 00:19:35,601
It was so violent.

489
00:19:35,669 --> 00:19:37,002
You're sure it was
a cop's nightstick?

490
00:19:37,070 --> 00:19:38,537
Well, i mean, it all
happened so fast,

491
00:19:38,605 --> 00:19:39,772
But that's what
it looked like.

492
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:41,273
But you didn't see
officer ramsey's face.

493
00:19:41,341 --> 00:19:42,441
No. just the stick.

494
00:19:42,509 --> 00:19:44,176
I just wish i knew
where to go from here.

495
00:19:44,244 --> 00:19:45,277
I checked around,
and it turns out

496
00:19:45,345 --> 00:19:46,846
One of his friends
brought dylan into the e.r.

497
00:19:46,913 --> 00:19:48,381
A kid named jake olmstead.

498
00:19:48,448 --> 00:19:50,516
Yeah, he's the one
who said it was
a skateboarding accident?

499
00:19:50,584 --> 00:19:52,184
That's what he said.
he just wiped out
at the park.

500
00:19:52,252 --> 00:19:53,886
What about dylan,
what'd he say?

501
00:19:53,954 --> 00:19:54,954
Nothing.

502
00:19:55,021 --> 00:19:56,622
He was barely conscious
before he died.

503
00:19:56,690 --> 00:19:59,792
Why would his friend
lie to protect
officer ramsey?

504
00:19:59,860 --> 00:20:00,993
Look, i don't know, honey.

505
00:20:01,061 --> 00:20:02,762
Now, i know you really want
to help this ghost,

506
00:20:02,829 --> 00:20:04,864
But i really
don't want you to take
unwarranted risks.

507
00:20:04,931 --> 00:20:06,799
And if this guy ramsey
killed a kid,

508
00:20:06,867 --> 00:20:08,067
And he's already trashed
your car--

509
00:20:08,135 --> 00:20:09,535
I'll stay
out of trouble.

510
00:20:09,603 --> 00:20:11,170
Don't i always?

511
00:20:14,541 --> 00:20:15,808
Not really.

