00:20:17,310 --> 00:20:19,111
Dr. james, come in.

513
00:20:19,179 --> 00:20:20,546
Thanks for calling.

514
00:20:20,614 --> 00:20:22,181
I've been reading
your work.

515
00:20:22,249 --> 00:20:23,682
Didn't know i had fans.

516
00:20:23,750 --> 00:20:25,184
Eh.

517
00:20:25,252 --> 00:20:28,654
I've been studying
how adolescents process
the death of a peer.

518
00:20:28,722 --> 00:20:30,689
Well, how're
the students
handling the loss?

519
00:20:30,757 --> 00:20:33,058
Eh, a lot of them
are struggling.

520
00:20:33,126 --> 00:20:34,827
Some come for help.
others...

521
00:20:34,895 --> 00:20:37,530
Wouldn't step a foot
through the door.

522
00:20:37,597 --> 00:20:41,133
What about the kids
who knew dylan well?
you know?

523
00:20:41,201 --> 00:20:43,769
Like his friend
who was with him when
the accident happened.

524
00:20:43,837 --> 00:20:45,771
Jake olmstead. right.

525
00:20:45,839 --> 00:20:47,873
Uh, checking in
with jake's still on
my to do list.

526
00:20:47,941 --> 00:20:49,141
Were they tight?

527
00:20:49,209 --> 00:20:51,243
No, actually.

528
00:20:51,311 --> 00:20:54,113
Jake and dylan
were on opposite ends
of the social hierarchy,

529
00:20:54,181 --> 00:20:55,648
With dylan pretty much
at the bottom.

530
00:20:55,715 --> 00:20:57,950
So dylan was
a shoved-in-your-
own-locker kind of kid?

531
00:20:58,018 --> 00:20:59,485
Not quite, no.

532
00:20:59,553 --> 00:21:00,586
He was a loner.

533
00:21:00,654 --> 00:21:02,621
Troubled family life.

534
00:21:02,689 --> 00:21:05,124
Acted out.
spent a lot of time
in the principal's office.

535
00:21:05,192 --> 00:21:06,392
And jake?

536
00:21:07,461 --> 00:21:08,494
Straight arrow.

537
00:21:08,562 --> 00:21:10,496
Baseball jock,
but with a brain.

538
00:21:10,564 --> 00:21:13,499
Plus, everyone likes him.

539
00:21:13,567 --> 00:21:15,634
How about dylan's
girlfriend?

540
00:21:15,702 --> 00:21:17,169
How's she dealing
with this?

541
00:21:17,237 --> 00:21:19,338
He had a girlfriend?

542
00:21:19,406 --> 00:21:21,607
Well, weren't he
and anne-marie
ramsey an item?

543
00:21:21,675 --> 00:21:23,008
You know anne-marie?

544
00:21:23,076 --> 00:21:25,177
I kinda know her dad.

545
00:21:25,245 --> 00:21:27,947
Huh.

546
00:21:28,014 --> 00:21:29,415
You got me.

547
00:21:29,483 --> 00:21:31,750
It's hard to keep track
of the hook-ups.

548
00:21:31,818 --> 00:21:33,652
Don't think
i ever saw her
with dylan, though.

549
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:34,687
Jake, sometimes.

550
00:21:34,754 --> 00:21:36,655
But not dylan.

551
00:21:38,492 --> 00:21:39,725
You know, i don't mean
to overstep,

552
00:21:39,793 --> 00:21:44,163
But if you could
use a hand,

553
00:21:44,231 --> 00:21:46,198
I'd be more than happy
to donate my therapy
services

554
00:21:46,266 --> 00:21:47,399
For a couple of hours
a week, you know?

555
00:21:47,467 --> 00:21:48,901
Just until
things calm down.

556
00:21:50,270 --> 00:21:51,770
I'd need to clear it
with the administration,

557
00:21:51,838 --> 00:21:52,872
But of course.

558
00:21:52,939 --> 00:21:54,139
That's very generous.

559
00:21:54,207 --> 00:21:56,475
I could start by talking
to jake olmstead.

560
00:21:56,543 --> 00:21:57,610
Great.

561
00:22:01,414 --> 00:22:02,648
that's him.

562
00:22:02,716 --> 00:22:04,283
I recognize him
from the team photo.

563
00:22:08,922 --> 00:22:10,422
Jake, right?

564
00:22:10,490 --> 00:22:12,424
I'm dr. eli james.
and this is
melinda gordon.

565
00:22:16,329 --> 00:22:17,630
What do you want?

566
00:22:17,697 --> 00:22:19,331
I'm working
with mitch larson.

567
00:22:19,399 --> 00:22:20,366
I'm a psychologist.

568
00:22:20,433 --> 00:22:21,534
A grief counselor.

569
00:22:21,601 --> 00:22:22,768
I don't need a shrink.

570
00:22:22,836 --> 00:22:24,036
You sure about that?

571
00:22:24,104 --> 00:22:25,571
Weren't you
with dylan hale
the night he died?

572
00:22:27,207 --> 00:22:28,140
Who told you that?

573
00:22:28,208 --> 00:22:30,309
It was in
the hospital records.

574
00:22:30,377 --> 00:22:32,411
Losing a friend can
be very traumatic.

575
00:22:32,479 --> 00:22:33,879
It helps
to talk about it.

576
00:22:33,947 --> 00:22:35,347
Look, i don't want
to talk to you.

577
00:22:38,451 --> 00:22:39,385
I'm fine.

578
00:22:39,452 --> 00:22:41,854
And i'm late
for practice.

579
00:22:44,925 --> 00:22:46,425
I can see why
he's so popular.

580
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:09,315
You just got something
off that car, didn't you?

581
00:23:09,382 --> 00:23:11,183
Good car.

582
00:23:11,251 --> 00:23:13,419
I think those kids
are harassing
officer ramsey.

583
00:23:13,486 --> 00:23:15,254
You're sure it's not
the other way around?

584
00:23:15,322 --> 00:23:16,622
How can they harass him?

585
00:23:16,690 --> 00:23:17,990
Vandalism.

586
00:23:18,058 --> 00:23:20,225
And i'm not just
talking about,
like, tping trees.

587
00:23:20,293 --> 00:23:21,827
It was vicious.

588
00:23:21,895 --> 00:23:23,128
They tore apart
his house.

589
00:23:23,196 --> 00:23:24,196
Wow.

590
00:23:24,264 --> 00:23:25,965
Take one cop feeling shamed
and powerless

591
00:23:26,032 --> 00:23:27,433
After a shooting incident,

592
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:29,234
Add a little ptsd,

593
00:23:29,302 --> 00:23:30,736
And pow!

594
00:23:30,804 --> 00:23:33,138
Vandalism like that
could've pushed him
over the edge.

595
00:23:41,815 --> 00:23:44,149
You're late.

596
00:23:44,217 --> 00:23:46,719
Where the hell
have you been?

597
00:23:46,786 --> 00:23:48,621
What difference
does it make?

598
00:23:48,688 --> 00:23:50,189
I'm your father.

599
00:23:52,826 --> 00:23:53,759
Who you been with?

600
00:23:53,827 --> 00:23:55,060
None of your
damn business.

601
00:23:55,128 --> 00:23:56,562
Don't talk to me
like that.

602
00:23:56,630 --> 00:23:58,831
You want to know
where i was so bad?

603
00:23:58,898 --> 00:24:01,734
I was at
a candlelight vigil
for dylan hale.

604
00:24:01,801 --> 00:24:03,702
Now, why would you
do that?

605
00:24:03,770 --> 00:24:04,937
You didn't even know him.

606
00:24:05,005 --> 00:24:06,572
Everybody was there.

607
00:24:06,640 --> 00:24:07,840
It would have looked
weird if i didn't go.

608
00:24:07,907 --> 00:24:10,709
I don't care
what it looks like.

609
00:24:10,777 --> 00:24:12,177
I saw you talking
to that woman.

610
00:24:12,245 --> 00:24:13,178
What woman?

611
00:24:13,246 --> 00:24:14,947
Melinda gordon.

612
00:24:15,015 --> 00:24:16,248
What'd you say to her?

613
00:24:16,316 --> 00:24:17,916
It's none
of your business.

614
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:22,788
It is my business.

615
00:24:22,856 --> 00:24:24,690
You are my business.

616
00:24:24,758 --> 00:24:26,759
I didn't
say anything.

617
00:24:26,826 --> 00:24:28,193
Now, leave me alone.

618
00:24:30,997 --> 00:24:32,131
Who's out there?

619
00:24:32,198 --> 00:24:34,667
Which one of your idiot
friends is outside?

620
00:24:41,007 --> 00:24:42,374
Dylan?

621
00:24:45,011 --> 00:24:46,178
What did you say?

622
00:24:46,246 --> 00:24:48,480
What's the difference?

623
00:24:48,548 --> 00:24:50,949
It's done.

624
00:24:51,017 --> 00:24:52,551
Nothing will
bring him back.

625
00:24:55,722 --> 00:24:58,624
Hey.

626
00:24:58,692 --> 00:25:01,260
Gotta watch your
step now more than
ever, anne-marie.

627
00:25:03,296 --> 00:25:05,731
I don't want
my little girl
getting hurt.

628
00:25:14,951 --> 00:25:16,651
Pb & j, your favorite.

629
00:25:16,719 --> 00:25:17,986
No trading, ok?

630
00:25:18,054 --> 00:25:20,522
Not even if abby
has maple syrup?

631
00:25:20,590 --> 00:25:22,691
Maple syrup?
for lunch?

632
00:25:22,759 --> 00:25:24,226
What is that?

633
00:25:24,293 --> 00:25:25,727
That's my sticker book.

634
00:25:27,096 --> 00:25:28,830
Aiden!

635
00:25:28,898 --> 00:25:29,931
Those are
mommy's car tags.

636
00:25:29,999 --> 00:25:31,266
Where did you
get these?

637
00:25:31,334 --> 00:25:33,902
From daddy. he left them
on the counter for me.

638
00:25:33,970 --> 00:25:35,604
He knows i like
shiny stickers.

639
00:25:35,671 --> 00:25:37,105
Aren't they cool?

640
00:25:37,173 --> 00:25:39,941
Yes, very cool.

641
00:25:40,009 --> 00:25:41,843
All right, out
to the bus stop.
come on.

642
00:25:41,911 --> 00:25:43,078
I'm gonna hold on
to that.

643
00:25:45,181 --> 00:25:46,281
There you go.

644
00:25:46,349 --> 00:25:48,717
All right?
let me see you.

645
00:25:48,785 --> 00:25:49,751
Mwah. handsome.

646
00:25:49,819 --> 00:25:51,987
Knock 'em dead,
big guy.
you, too.

647
00:25:52,054 --> 00:25:52,988
I'll walk you to the bus
in a second, honey.

648
00:25:53,055 --> 00:25:53,989
Ok, mommy.

649
00:25:54,056 --> 00:25:55,991
Eli the chauffeur,
at your service.

650
00:25:56,058 --> 00:25:59,027
Look where
the registration tags
for my car have been,

651
00:25:59,095 --> 00:26:00,028
Aiden's sticker book.

652
00:26:00,096 --> 00:26:01,430
So they really
were expired?

653
00:26:01,497 --> 00:26:03,732
Yeah, and i thought
ramsey had had
my car got towed.

654
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:05,233
Well, he's still the reason
it got shredded.

655
00:26:05,301 --> 00:26:07,202
I'm not sure about that.

656
00:26:07,270 --> 00:26:09,571
'cause jim said
that he was poking
around the hospital,

657
00:26:09,639 --> 00:26:11,206
Asking a bunch of
questions about dylan,

658
00:26:11,274 --> 00:26:13,575
And if he had done
something, wouldn't
he have known?

659
00:26:13,643 --> 00:26:14,910
Could be he's trying
to figure out

660
00:26:14,977 --> 00:26:16,211
If anyone knew
he was involved.

661
00:26:16,279 --> 00:26:17,412
Yeah, i don't know
about that.

662
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:18,680
Didn't you get
my text?

663
00:26:18,748 --> 00:26:20,081
I hadn't checked today.

664
00:26:20,149 --> 00:26:22,083
Oh, well,
jim also found out

665
00:26:22,151 --> 00:26:24,186
That ramsey came
to pick up
dylan's things.

666
00:26:24,253 --> 00:26:25,821
His clothes,
skateboard.

667
00:26:25,888 --> 00:26:27,456
Anything that he had
brought with him
at the hospital.

668
00:26:27,523 --> 00:26:28,690
Wait. dylan's parents
didn't do that?

669
00:26:28,758 --> 00:26:30,559
Apparently not.

670
00:26:30,626 --> 00:26:33,028
What if he's getting rid
of incriminating evidence?

671
00:26:33,095 --> 00:26:34,796
Look, weeks
after the accident?

672
00:26:34,864 --> 00:26:36,198
Look, remember,
i told you

673
00:26:36,265 --> 00:26:38,433
I didn't actually
see ramsey hit him
with the nightstick.

674
00:26:41,971 --> 00:26:42,971
Dylan.

675
00:26:43,039 --> 00:26:44,372
Why don't you
believe it? he did it.

676
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:45,974
He's guilty.

677
00:26:46,042 --> 00:26:47,809
I just think
there's more to
the story than that.

678
00:26:47,877 --> 00:26:49,144
You don't understand.

679
00:26:49,212 --> 00:26:51,413
You vandalized
his house.
you tormented him.

680
00:26:51,481 --> 00:26:52,714
He had it coming.

681
00:26:52,782 --> 00:26:55,417
No one has the right
to come between people
like he did.

682
00:26:55,485 --> 00:26:57,185
Not when they're in love.

683
00:26:59,689 --> 00:27:01,089
Hello?

684
00:27:01,157 --> 00:27:02,390
Hey, mitch.

685
00:27:02,458 --> 00:27:03,658
Yeah, of course,
i remember you.

686
00:27:03,726 --> 00:27:05,861
You're my newest--
well, maybe my only--fan.

687
00:27:05,928 --> 00:27:08,663
No, i haven't had a chance
to talk to her yet. why?

688
00:27:10,099 --> 00:27:12,067
Ok, thanks.

689
00:27:12,134 --> 00:27:13,535
Anne-marie hasn't been
to school in 2 days.

690
00:27:15,404 --> 00:27:16,872
Has anyone talked
to her father?

691
00:27:16,939 --> 00:27:19,541
They called the house,
no answer. why?

692
00:27:19,609 --> 00:27:20,842
hopefully nothing,

693
00:27:20,910 --> 00:27:22,143
Except he saw me
talking to her

694
00:27:22,211 --> 00:27:23,678
And he didn't
look pleased.

695
00:27:28,117 --> 00:27:29,551
Give me a second.

696
00:27:34,724 --> 00:27:36,625
Ms. gordon, i don't
have time right now --

697
00:27:36,692 --> 00:27:37,926
I don't want
to start any trouble,

698
00:27:37,994 --> 00:27:39,127
But it's about
your daughter.

699
00:27:39,195 --> 00:27:40,195
What about her?

700
00:27:40,263 --> 00:27:42,130
She's missed school
2 days in a row.

701
00:27:42,198 --> 00:27:43,632
You're tracking my kid's
whereabouts now?

702
00:27:43,699 --> 00:27:45,867
I just want
to make sure she's ok.

703
00:27:45,935 --> 00:27:47,836
I'll deal with it.

704
00:27:50,006 --> 00:27:51,473
Look, she's troubled
about something

705
00:27:51,541 --> 00:27:52,574
And i think i can help.

706
00:27:52,642 --> 00:27:54,643
I don't. now if
you'll excuse me,

707
00:27:54,710 --> 00:27:56,111
I'm in the middle
of an investigation.

708
00:27:56,178 --> 00:27:58,280
Yeah, is that why
you have dylan's things?

709
00:27:58,347 --> 00:28:00,015
Last time
i asked you about him

710
00:28:00,082 --> 00:28:02,450
You said that his death
was an accident, not a crime.

711
00:28:02,518 --> 00:28:04,553
You said that you
didn't know anything.

712
00:28:11,294 --> 00:28:12,928
You need to leave.

713
00:28:14,830 --> 00:28:17,198
Yeah, ok.

714
00:28:17,266 --> 00:28:18,266
Sorry.

715
00:28:20,002 --> 00:28:22,170
Eli, on phone:
what do you mean,
it wasn't a nightstick?

716
00:28:22,238 --> 00:28:23,638
It looked like a nightstick,

717
00:28:23,706 --> 00:28:25,173
But it was actually
a baseball bat.

718
00:28:25,241 --> 00:28:27,375
Ramsey beat dylan's head
in with a baseball bat?

719
00:28:27,443 --> 00:28:29,110
Melinda, on phone:
not ramsey. jake.

720
00:28:29,178 --> 00:28:31,079
Clean-cut
jock jake? why?

721
00:28:31,147 --> 00:28:32,080
I don't know.

722
00:28:32,148 --> 00:28:33,582
The ghost said
something about

723
00:28:33,649 --> 00:28:34,583
If people
love each other,

724
00:28:34,650 --> 00:28:35,817
They should be together.

725
00:28:35,885 --> 00:28:37,018
Eli, on phone:
you're thinking

726
00:28:37,086 --> 00:28:38,219
This is how jake
stopped their romance?

727
00:28:38,287 --> 00:28:41,022
By whacking
his competition
in the skull?

728
00:28:41,090 --> 00:28:42,991
It seems unlikely,
i know.

729
00:28:43,059 --> 00:28:46,428
And if that's true,
why has dylan been
blaming officer ramsey?

730
00:28:46,495 --> 00:28:47,796
I don't know, and i'd like
to talk to jake,

731
00:28:47,863 --> 00:28:49,664
But i don't have a car.

732
00:28:49,732 --> 00:28:51,566
I'll come by the store
after my next class.

733
00:28:51,634 --> 00:28:53,234
Teach quick. bye.

734
00:28:53,302 --> 00:28:54,569
Surprise!
surprise!

735
00:28:56,973 --> 00:28:58,139
Hi!

736
00:28:58,207 --> 00:28:59,441
Oh, my gosh.

737
00:28:59,508 --> 00:29:01,743
check--
check it out, mom.

738
00:29:01,811 --> 00:29:04,212
It's an acadia.

739
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:05,213
Oh, my goodness.

740
00:29:05,281 --> 00:29:06,481
It's got a remote.

741
00:29:06,549 --> 00:29:08,283
And a camera
so you won't
back into anything.

742
00:29:08,351 --> 00:29:10,051
Nice.

743
00:29:10,119 --> 00:29:11,753
it's got
3 rows of seats, too.

744
00:29:11,821 --> 00:29:14,689
So we can carpool with
my whole soccer team.

745
00:29:14,757 --> 00:29:15,724
Oh, great.

746
00:29:15,791 --> 00:29:17,425
Yeah.

747
00:29:17,493 --> 00:29:18,760
come on in.

748
00:29:18,828 --> 00:29:20,128
I know how much
you loved that old car,

749
00:29:20,196 --> 00:29:22,397
But i just remember
it took you about
a year to pick it,

750
00:29:22,465 --> 00:29:23,598
So, i hope you
don't mind if we --

751
00:29:23,666 --> 00:29:24,933
Mind? why
would i mind?

752
00:29:25,001 --> 00:29:26,635
And i love you.

753
00:29:26,702 --> 00:29:28,103
Both of you.

754
00:29:28,170 --> 00:29:30,138
I'm sorry
about your old car.

755
00:29:30,206 --> 00:29:32,107
I didn't know they were
stickers for grown-ups.

756
00:29:32,174 --> 00:29:33,608
It's ok.

757
00:29:33,676 --> 00:29:34,643
We did good?

758
00:29:34,710 --> 00:29:35,944
You did great.

759
00:29:36,012 --> 00:29:37,412
Listen, tonight,
when i get home,

760
00:29:37,480 --> 00:29:38,847
We'll all
take a drive
together, ok?

761
00:29:38,914 --> 00:29:41,716
For now,
there's somebody
i need to talk to.

762
00:29:41,784 --> 00:29:42,751
Go crazy.

763
00:29:42,818 --> 00:29:44,052
Yay!
all right.

764
00:29:44,120 --> 00:29:45,186
I love you,
i love you.
i love you.

765
00:29:45,254 --> 00:29:46,888
Ooh, i can't believe
this is for me!

766
00:29:46,956 --> 00:29:48,490
Here, pal.
hang on to that.

767
00:29:51,127 --> 00:29:52,093
Ok.

768
00:29:52,161 --> 00:29:53,762
i'm excited!

769
